main event: A professor and engineer in Montevideo, Uruguay observed an unidentified elongated elliptical object moving at high speed and high altitude on September 12, 1962.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be around 15-20 meters long by 5 meters wide.
The object was moving horizontally at a high speed over the city, with a rotating motion.
The object accelerated and disappeared in the distance.
The object oscillated slightly during its flight.
The object was observed at an altitude of around 3,000 to 5,000 meters.
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
